 to actual tests, potentially placing these sources in `src/test/scala`. It might also be possible to create Java or Scala sources there and set up a two-phase compile for the test Scala, though that feels a bit messy. It’s interesting how the dynamic access call interacts with singleton modules as `Ident`. So much to think about!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering fixture file structure**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how a fixture file might break the one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and the generated test class files. They want a separate Scala test file for each dynamic class, so should I keep the fixture in the same `ValueEnumMacrosTest.scala` file? But if we precompile the same file, I can't split it. Maybe I need a second file for the fixture that doesn’t have \\\"Test\\\" in the name. Would that be okay?\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JkbuTLhEkRZNTXknmf0XzgmB|fc_00c2bac56877bcc5016a3e6ce5e09081959c7311134c607685", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find /tmp/metadata-forge-gradle -path '*com.beachape/enumeratum_3/1.9.0*' -type f | head"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1102, "output": 2112, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46222, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782475969667, "responseId": "resp_00c2bac56877bcc5016a3e6cc46d488195aebd16599b4f95fa"}}
