ixture first before testing to have correct access to types like `PrecompiledDraft`. Using `import com...PrecompiledDraft` might increase the chances of referencing correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Understanding package and ValueOf**\\n\\nI've noticed that the same package's top-level can be referenced by its simple name in the type. However, the synthesis of `ValueOf` is independent of that. If something is precompiled and at the top level, then Class.forName should be able to load it. I think it's essential to keep this in mind while working on the macro and ensuring that everything links correctly together. It sounds clearer when put that way!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_AhNcr2pPyyZ75RkcSLM6Uef2|fc_00c2bac56877bcc5016a3e6d250cf481959a5bf90e1d8d46be", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.beachape/enumeratum-macros_3/1.9.0/src/test/scala/com_beachape/enumeratum_macros_3/ValueEnumMacroEntries.scala", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_beachape.enumeratum_macros_3\n\nsealed abstract class PrecompiledArticleStatus(val value: String)\n\ncase object PrecompiledDraft extends PrecompiledArticleStatus(\"draft\")\ncase object PrecompiledPublished extends PrecompiledArticleStatus(\"published\")\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1752, "output": 1344, "cacheRead": 48640, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51736, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782476052025, "responseId": "resp_00c2bac56877bcc5016a3e6d14bdbc8195b70441dc79c0fdc4"}}
